cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.HC, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the use of text-mining and machine learning techniques to analyze social media communication about Media Architecture. This involves aspects of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as well as the use of algorithms to sort and organize discourse (cs.SI). The topic of Media Architecture itself involves the use of digital infrastructures and networked places, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and systems and control (cs.SD).
